"title": "8848: worldliness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8848: worldliness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The sinful tendency to conform to the world, to be contrasted with the biblical command to maintain contact with the world while avoiding becoming like the world. Believers are called to live in the world, while not being of the world. This attitude is supremely exemplified in the ministry of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>The paradox of God's love for a sinful world</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:15-1John2:16\">1JN 2:15–2:16</a></p>\n<h2>God's people are called to be separate from the world, yet a source of blessing to it</h2>\n<h3>The example of Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:1-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:1–12:3</a></strong> <em>The life of Abraham illustrates the important biblical balance, called to separation from his native environment to be a blessing to the nations.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:7\">GEN 15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:18\">GEN 18:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:8\">GAL 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>The example of others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:56-Gen41:57\">GEN 41:56–41:57</a> <em>Joseph</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:48-Dan2:49\">DAN 2:48–2:49</a> <em>Daniel and his friends</em></p>\n<h2>Conformity to the pagan standards of the OT world disparaged</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:28\">LEV 18:28</a> <em>with respect to sexual perversion</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:5\">1SA 8:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:7\">1KI 21:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:7-1Kgs11:8\">1KI 11:7–11:8</a> <em>with respect to idolatry</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:19\">ISA 13:19</a> <em>with respect to pride</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:6\">ZEC 4:6</a></p>\n<h2>God's concern for the nations of the world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:6\">ISA 49:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:11\">JON 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:2\">REV 22:2</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is a model of the required balance of being in the world but not of it</h2>\n<h3>He was in the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16-John3:17\">JHN 3:16–3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:5\">JHN 9:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:28\">JHN 16:28</a></p>\n<h3>He was not of the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:23\">JHN 8:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:5-Luke4:8\">LUK 4:5–4:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:8-Matt4:10\">MAT 4:8–4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:14\">JHN 17:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:36\">JHN 18:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:1\">1JN 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>He was a friend of the disreputable</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:19\">MAT 11:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:16\">MRK 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:44-Luke7:48\">LUK 7:44–7:48</a></p>\n<h3>He was concerned for outsiders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:24-Mark7:30\">MRK 7:24–7:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:21-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:21–15:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are called to live in the world, while not being of it</h2>\n<h3>They have been chosen out of the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:19\">JHN 15:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:14\">JHN 17:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:16\">JHN 17:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:17\">2CO 6:17</a></p>\n<h3>They must avoid conformity with the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">ROM 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:3-1Thess4:5\">1TH 4:3–4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:10\">2TI 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:12\">TIT 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:27\">JAS 1:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:14-1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:14–1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:3-1Pet4:4\">1PE 4:3–4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:15\">1JN 2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:4\">1JN 5:4</a></p>\n<h3>They must maintain contact with the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:9-1Cor5:10\">1CO 5:9–5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:11\">JHN 17:11</a></p>\n<h3>They must do good in the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:10\">GAL 6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a></p>",
